<file path="app/AGENTS.md">
# Anfitrion – AI Agents Guide

This document defines how AI coding agents should work in this repository.

---

# Project Overview

Anfitrion is a lightweight SaaS for managing short-term rental properties (Airbnb, cabins, small inns).

Primary users:

- Individual hosts
- Small property managers (1–10 properties)

Core features:

- Reservation calendar
- Property management
- Guest management
- iCal integration (Airbnb / Booking)
- Reservation tracking

Tech stack:

Frontend

- Next.js (App Router)
- React
- TypeScript
- TailwindCSS

Backend

- Supabase
- Postgres

UI

- Tailwind
- Custom UI components in `/components/ui`

Calendar

- react-big-calendar

---

# Code Architecture

Project structure:

app/
dashboard/
acomodacoes/
reservas/
hospedes/
configuracoes/

components/
ui/
layout/

lib/
supabase-browser.ts

Rules:

- UI components must stay in `/components/ui`
- Layout components must stay in `/components/layout`
- Pages must remain inside `/app`
- Database access must go through Supabase client

---

# Database Principles

Tables:

properties
reservations
guests
services
reservation_services

Rules:

- Always reference properties using `property_id`
- Use ISO date format for reservations
- Prevent reservation overlap using Postgres constraints

Reservation structure:

id
property_id
guest_id
label
start_date
end_date
status
origin
notes
created_at

---

# Calendar Rules

Calendar must:

- support month view
- support week view
- show reservations per property
- display reservations visually centered
- use color based on reservation status

Reservation status colors:

confirmed → orange
pending → blue
cancelled → gray
completed → green

---

# UI Guidelines

Design goals:

- Minimal
- Clean SaaS style
- Fast interface

Primary palette:

Navy blue
Dark orange

Components should use Tailwind utilities.

Avoid heavy UI libraries.

---

# Coding Guidelines

Prefer:

- small components
- readable code
- explicit typing

Avoid:

- overly abstract patterns
- unnecessary dependencies
- large monolithic components

---

# AI Agent Instructions

When editing code:

1. Do not rewrite entire files unless necessary
2. Prefer minimal diffs
3. Preserve existing architecture
4. Maintain TypeScript types
5. Follow Tailwind style conventions

When creating features:

1. Start from data model
2. Add UI
3. Connect Supabase
4. Validate UX

---

# Future Modules

Planned features:

- Guest CRM
- Cleaning checklist
- Service add-ons
- Admin console
- Payment tracking
