# Anfitrion — Project Context Documentation

This document describes the full context of the Anfitrion project.

It should be used by:

- new developers joining the project
- AI coding agents (Codex, Claude, ChatGPT)
- contributors
- maintainers

The goal is to ensure full understanding of the system architecture, product vision, and development status.

---

# 1. Project Overview

Anfitrion is a lightweight SaaS designed to manage short-term rental properties.

Target users:

- Airbnb hosts
- Cabin owners
- Small inns
- Property managers managing up to 10 units

The goal is to provide a **simple and intuitive system for small hosts**, avoiding the complexity and high cost of traditional PMS platforms.

Core principles:

- simple
- visual
- intuitive
- mobile-friendly
- low cost

---

# 2. Product Vision

Most small hosts currently manage reservations using:

- spreadsheets
- WhatsApp
- manual notes
- Airbnb interface only

Anfitrion solves this by providing:

- a centralized calendar
- guest management
- reservation tracking
- operational dashboard

Future vision:

An affordable **mini PMS for small property managers**.

---

# 3. Target Market

Primary audience:

Hosts with:

1 to 10 properties

Examples:

- cabins
- chalets
- small guest houses
- apartments
- rural tourism stays

Secondary audience:

Property managers managing multiple Airbnb accounts.

---

# 4. Technology Stack

Frontend:

- Next.js (App Router)
- React
- TypeScript
- TailwindCSS

UI system:

- custom UI components
- Tailwind based
- mobile-first design

Calendar:

- react-big-calendar

Backend:

- Supabase

Database:

- PostgreSQL

Authentication:

- Supabase Auth

---

# 5. Core Product Modules

Current modules:

Dashboard
Properties (Acomodações)
Reservations
Guests (planned)
Settings

---

# 6. Current Database Schema

## properties

Represents each accommodation unit.

Examples:

Cabana A
Cabana B
Apartamento 101

Fields:

id  
user_id  
name  
status  
location  
co_host  
airbnb_ical_url  
booking_ical_url  
created_at

---

## reservations

Represents a reservation period.

Fields:

id  
property_id  
guest_id  
label  
start_date  
end_date  
status  
origin  
notes  
created_at

Important:

Reservation overlap is prevented using a PostgreSQL constraint.

---

## guests (planned)

Represents guest profiles.

Fields:

id  
name  
phone  
email  
cpf  
address  
created_at

Guests may have multiple reservations.

---

## services (planned)

Represents optional services offered by the property.

Examples:

breakfast  
tour  
cleaning  
late checkout

Fields:

id  
name  
price

---

## reservation_services (planned)

Relationship between reservations and services.

Fields:

id  
reservation_id  
service_id  
price

---

# 7. Reservation Logic

Reservations include:

label

Example:

"Casal de Floripa"

This is used as the main visual identifier in the calendar.

Guests can optionally be attached to reservations.

---

# 8. Calendar System

The calendar is the central UI of the product.

Library used:

react-big-calendar

Supported views:

month  
week

Visual improvements implemented:

- centered reservation bars
- diagonal edges for check-in / check-out
- color by reservation status

Future improvements:

- timeline per property
- cleaning blocks
- maintenance blocks

---

# 9. Dashboard

The dashboard contains:

Stat cards
Reservation calendar

Cards planned:

Reservations today  
Check-ins today  
Check-outs today  
Monthly occupancy

Purpose:

Provide operational visibility.

---

# 10. UI Design Principles

The UI must be:

friendly  
colorful  
intuitive

Reference inspirations:

Airbnb Host Dashboard  
Notion  
Stripe Dashboard

Primary palette:

Navy blue  
Dark orange

Status colors:

confirmed → green  
pending → blue  
cancelled → red

Components used:

Card  
Button  
Input  
Select  
Modal  
StatCard  
Table

---

# 11. UX Principles

Design rules:

mobile-first  
minimal cognitive load  
large touch targets  
clear visual feedback

Hosts should understand the system without reading documentation.

---

# 12. Current Implemented Features

Working features:

Authentication via Supabase  
Property creation  
Reservation creation  
Calendar display  
Reservation conflict detection  
Database overlap protection  
Responsive layout  
Sidebar navigation  
Dashboard calendar

---

# 13. Current Limitations

Features not yet implemented:

Guest CRM  
Reservation editing  
Reservation table view  
Cleaning workflow  
Booking.com integration  
Airbnb iCal sync automation  
Admin console  
Payment tracking

---

# 14. Planned Roadmap

Phase 1 (MVP)

